ints. Designed for professionals, workshop settings, and self-learners, the book demonstrates several databases so the reader can follow along in a hands-on approach. Each chapter also has a set of questions and follow up projects to reinforce comprehension of the material. Features: Includes demonstration and solution implementations on the major Database Management Systems (MySQL, Oracle, and Microsoft SQL Server) and computing platforms (Linux/UNIX, MacOS, Windows) to be applicable for nearly every student and professional End of chapter exercises to enhance comprehension of topics  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aComputer security. 0aDatabase security. 4aData. 4aE-Commerce. 4aIT Management & Security. 7aCOMPUTERS / Electronic Commerce (see also headings under BUSINESS & ECONOMICS / ECommerce).2bisacsh  aLinux/UNIX.  aMacOS.  aMicrosoft SQL Server.  aMySQL.  aOracle.  aWindows.  acomputer science.  acybersecurity.  adata analytics.  adata science.  adatabase normalization.  ae-commerce.  areferential integrity.  atransactions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI AI COLLECTIONz978311157353308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024z978311156434008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI and ITGP STEM IT PACKAGEz978311157407308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97816839266100 cprintz978168392663440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168392662740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781683926627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781683926627/original  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  a978-3-11-156434-0  MLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024b2024  a978-3-11